{"id":1316827747,"question_id":3491,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"2 weeks, 2 days","timestamp":1720640273,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"75 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1316827747/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Find the Maximum Length of Valid Subsequence II","memory":"128.8 MB","code":"class Solution {\npublic:\n    int maximumLength(vector<int>& nums, int k) {\n        vector<vector<int>> dp(k, vector<int>(k, 0));\n        int maxLen = 0;\n        \n        for (int num : nums) {\n            for (int j = 0; j < k; ++j) {\n                int remainder = num % k;\n                maxLen = max(maxLen, dp[remainder][j] = dp[j][remainder] + 1);\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return maxLen;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"find-the-maximum-length-of-valid-subsequence-ii","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
